label.value: calculated retina rod bipolar cell count

value.value: Any measurement that has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the retina rod bipolar cell count from one or both retinas.

label.value: central retina rod bipolar cell count to area ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the number of rod bipolar cells in the central retina is divided by the total area of the central retina. A rod bipolar cell is a neuron that is synapsed by rod photoreceptor cells but not by cone photoreceptor cells.

label.value: peripheral retina rod bipolar cell count to area ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the number of rod bipolar cells in the peripheral retina is divided by the total area of the peripheral retina. A rod bipolar cell is a neuron that is synapsed by rod photoreceptor cells but not by cone photoreceptor cells.

label.value: measurement of minimal stimulus needed to elicit evasive reaction

value.value: A measurement of thermal, mechanical, or chemical stimulus which causes the subject to take evasive action to avoid further stimulation.

label.value: measurement of minimal mechanical stimulus needed to elicit evasive reaction

value.value: A measurement of the pressure of liquid, gas, or solid stimulus which causes the subject to take evasive action to avoid further stimulation. This measurement is often interpreted as the threshold of pain.

label.value: liver adult Schistosoma mansoni worm count

value.value: Measurement of the total number of adult, that is, fully developed, Schistosoma mansoni trematode worms recovered from a specified sample or perfusate of liver from an infected subject.

label.value: percent protection by treatment for Schistosoma mansoni

value.value: A measurement of the degree to which the presentation of the Schistosomiasis disease state, i.e. infection with trematode worms of Schistosomiasis mansoni), has been reduced in a population as a result of some intervening treatment.

label.value: intestine tumor incidence/prevalence measurement

value.value: Any measurement in which the number of individuals in a study population that display intestine tumors at a point in time or develop intestine tumors within a determined period of time are compared to the total number of individuals in the study population. Often expressed as a percentage but could be expressed as a ratio. Intestine tumors are abnormal growths of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function, which occur in the intestine, the portion of the alimentary canal extending from the pyloric opening of the stomach to the anus.

label.value: intestine tumor measurement

value.value: The quantification of a parameter related to an abnormal growth of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function, which occurs in the intestine, the portion of the alimentary canal extending from the pyloric opening of the stomach to the anus.

label.value: percentage of study population developing intestine tumors during a period of time

value.value: The number of new cases of intestine tumors appearing in a study population during a certain period compared to the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage, but could be expressed as a ratio. Intestine tumors are abnormal growths of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function, which occur in the intestine, the portion of the alimentary canal extending from the pyloric opening of the stomach to the anus.

label.value: percentage of study population displaying intestine tumors at a point in time

value.value: The number of individuals in a study population which display intestine tumors at a certain point in time compared to the total number of individuals in the study population, expressed as a percentage or ratio. Intestine tumors are abnormal growths of tissue resulting from uncontrolled, progressive multiplication of cells and serving no physiological function, which occur in the intestine, the portion of the alimentary canal extending from the pyloric opening of the stomach to the anus.

label.value: liver iron measurement

value.value: Any measurement of iron, a heavy metal element that is vital to many biological processes, in liver, the large, dark-red organ located in the cranial portion of the abdomen of vertebrates, just behind or below the diaphragm, the functions of which include storage and filtration of blood, secretion of bile, detoxification of noxious substances, conversion of sugars into glycogen, synthesis and breakdown of fats, and synthesis of serum proteins.

label.value: liver iron amount

value.value: Measurement of the amount of the iron, a heavy metal element that is vital to many biological processes, in a specified sample of liver.

label.value: calculated liver iron amount

value.value: A measurement of the amount of the iron in a specified sample of liver, when that measurement has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

label.value: liver iron weight to liver weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of liver is divided by the weight of that liver sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: liver tumorous lesion iron weight to liver tumorous lesion weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of liver tumorous lesion is divided by the weight of that liver tumorous lesion sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: liver iron weight to liver metastastic tumorous lesion weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of liver metastastic tumorous lesion is divided by the weight of that liver metastastic tumorous lesion sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: tear morphological measurement

value.value: Measurement of the physical characteristics (volume, pH, chemical composition, etc.) of tears, the fluid secreted by the lacrimal glands by means of which the conjunctiva and cornea are kept moist.

label.value: tear volume measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the size of the three dimensional space of tears, the fluid secreted by the lacrimal glands by means of which the conjunctiva and cornea are kept moist.

label.value: calculated tear volume measurement

value.value: Any measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the size of the three dimensional space occupied by tears produced by an organism.

label.value: tear secretion rate

value.value: A measure of tears secreted per unit time.

label.value: measurement of minimal stimulus of cornea needed to elicit eyelid blinking

value.value: This measurement involves thermal, chemical, or mechanical stimulation of the cornea until the induction of eye blinking.

label.value: parasitic infection population measurement

value.value: This is any measurement which deals with parasitic infections in terms of population, geography or demographics.

label.value: lymphoma size measurement

value.value: Any measurement of the size of an individual tumorous lymphomatous lesion, or of the amount of the surrounding tissue occupied by tumorous lesions. A lymphoma is a tumor, usually malignant, made up of lymphocytes from lymphoid tissue or blood-forming organs.

label.value: calculated lymphoma size measurement

value.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process of a lymphomatous lesion, that is, a neoplasm or new growth of lymphocytes in which cell multiplication is more or less uncontrolled and progressive.

label.value: maximum tumor size decrease to pretreatment tumor size ratio

value.value: A calculated value (size of the tumor at the start of therapy minus minimal obtained tumor size, divided by tumor size at the start of therapy x 100) in which the maximum size reduction of a lymphoma is divided by the pretreatment size of the lymphoma and presented as a ratio, fraction or quotient, thus normalizing it to the pretreatment size of the lymphoma.

label.value: time from start of drug therapy to immunocytoma regrowth

value.value: The length of time elapsed between the beginning of drug therapy and the regrowth of immunocytoma(s).

label.value: time from therapy-induced maximal immunocytoma size decrease to regrowth of tumor to a diameter of 10 mm

value.value: The elapsed time between the maximal therapy-induced tumor size reduction to regrowth of the tumor to a diameter of ten millimeters.

label.value: soleus muscle weight

value.value: The weight of all or part of a soleus muscle, a deep muscle of the triceps surae group, in the superficial posterior compartment of the leg.

label.value: soleus muscle weight to body weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of the soleus muscle is divided by the total weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thereby normalizing it to body weight and, by extension, to the size of the organism.

label.value: capillary number to soleus muscle fiber number ratio

value.value: The total number of capillaries divided by the total number of skeletal muscle fibers within each soleus muscle histological cross‐section.

label.value: urine albumin level to urine osmolality ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of albumin in a specified volume of urine is divided by the osmolality of the same sample of urine.

label.value: liver MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from healthy liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle.

label.value: liver tumor MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from tumorous liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle.

label.value: calculated morphological liver measurement

value.value: A measurement of any parameter in a specified sample of liver, when that measurement has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

label.value: liver MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio (PD-weighted)

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from healthy liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle. A PD-weighted image relies on the proton density of the imaged material.

label.value: liver MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio (T2-weighted)

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from healthy liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle. A characteristic of a T2-weighted image is the high intensity signal of water versus a low intensity signal of bone or air.

label.value: liver tumor MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio (PD-weighted)

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from tumorous liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle. A PD-weighted image relies on the proton density of the imaged material.

label.value: liver tumor MRI signal intensity to paravertebral muscle MRI signal intensity ratio (T2-weighted)

value.value: A calculated value in which the signal intensity value from tumorous liver tissue is divided by the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle of the same subject and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to the signal intensity value from paravertebral muscle. A characteristic of a T2-weighted image is the high intensity signal of water versus a low intensity signal of bone or air.

label.value: liver iron weight to liver wet weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of wet liver is divided by the weight of that liver sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: liver iron weight to liver dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of dessicated liver is divided by the weight of that liver sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. The dry weight of the liver may also be estimated by subtracting the weight of water in the liver sample from the total weight of the liver sample.

label.value: liver tumorous lesion iron weight to liver tumorous lesion wet weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of wet liver tumorous lesion is divided by the weight of that liver sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

label.value: liver tumorous lesion iron weight to liver tumorous lesion dry weight ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of iron in a specified sample of dessicated liver tumorous lesion is divided by the weight of that liver sample and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage. The dry weight of the liver tumorous lesion may also be estimated by subtracting the weight of water in the liver tumorous lesion sample from the total weight of the liver tumorous lesion sample.

label.value: calculated plasma nifedipine level

value.value: Any measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of nifedipine, a potent vasodilator agent with calcium antagonistic action, in a specified sample of plasma.

label.value: calculated plasma triglyceride level

value.value: A measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation, of the amount of triglycerides in a specified volume of plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended. Triglycerides are any of a group of lipids that are esters formed from one molecule of glycerol and three molecules of one or more fatty acids and are widespread in adipose tissue.

label.value: plasma triglyceride level area under curve

value.value: A calculated measurement in which a series of measurements of the amount of triglycerides in a specified volume of plasma is plotted against time for a single individual and the extent of the two dimensional region bounded by the curve and the axes of the graph is determined.

label.value: metastatic subcutaneous tumor weight

value.value: The weight of one or more metastatic tumors measured after growing in the hypodermis, any subcutaneous position in the body. A metastatic subcutaneous tumor is a secondary, abnormal, subcutaneous growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells from the place where they first formed.

label.value: metastatic liver tumor number

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of metastatic tumors in the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: number of small metastatic liver tumors

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of small (< 1 mm) metastatic tumors in the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.

label.value: number of medium-sized metastatic liver tumors

value.value: A value or quantity determined by count of medium-sized (1-3 mm) metastatic tumors in the liver. A metastatic tumor in the liver is a secondary, abnormal growth of tissue resulting from the spread of cancer cells to the liver from the place where they first formed.
